# SENTINEL PROJECT RULES

## Project Context
You are building Sentinel, an AI-powered equity and crypto screening platform.
The full project plan is in SENTINEL_PROJECT_PLAN.md at the project root.
ALWAYS read the relevant section of SENTINEL_PROJECT_PLAN.md before implementing any feature.

## Tech Stack (do not deviate)
- Next.js 15 with App Router (TypeScript strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4 (dark theme, design tokens in globals.css)
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Realtime)
- Financial Datasets API (primary data source)
- Unusual Whales API (options flow)
- Alpha Vantage API (technical indicators)
- Anthropic Claude API via @anthropic-ai/sdk (AI analysis)
- Discord.js (bot alerts)
- Lightweight Charts by TradingView (price charts)
- Recharts (score visualizations)

## Architecture Rules
1. All API calls go through wrapper functions in lib/ — never call APIs directly from components
2. All database queries go through lib/db.ts — never import Supabase client in components
3. API routes in app/api/ are thin — they call lib/ functions and return responses
4. Components are presentational — they receive data via props or React Server Components
5. The Discord bot is a SEPARATE process (discord/bot.ts), NOT inside Next.js
6. Cron jobs are Vercel Cron routes in app/api/cron/ that call lib/ functions

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types. Define interfaces in lib/utils/types.ts
- Use async/await, never .then() chains
- All functions that can fail must have try/catch with meaningful error messages
- Use early returns to reduce nesting
- All numeric formatting (currency, percentages, large numbers) goes through lib/utils/format.ts
- Use date-fns for all date manipulation — never raw Date math

## Database Rules
- Schema is defined in SENTINEL_PROJECT_PLAN.md under "Database Schema (Supabase)"
- Always use parameterized queries (Supabase client handles this)
- Always check for .error on Supabase responses before using .data
- Use upsert with onConflict for tables with unique constraints
- Batch inserts where possible (don't insert 3000 rows in a loop)

## API Integration Rules
- Financial Datasets: wrapper in lib/financial-datasets.ts
  - Respect rate limits (pay-as-you-go: reasonable, Developer: 1000/min)
  - Cache responses in Supabase — don't re-fetch the same data within 24h
  - All endpoints documented at https://docs.financialdatasets.ai
- Unusual Whales: wrapper in lib/unusual-whales.ts
  - Docs at https://api.unusualwhales.com/docs
- Alpha Vantage: wrapper in lib/alpha-vantage.ts
  - Free tier: 25 calls/day. Be aggressive about caching.
- Claude API: wrapper in lib/claude.ts
  - Always use claude-sonnet-4-20250514 model
  - Always set max_tokens: 4096
  - All prompts must request JSON-only responses (no markdown, no preamble)
  - Always validate JSON parsing with try/catch — AI responses can be malformed
  - Store raw AI responses in JSONB columns for debugging

## Scoring System Rules
- Sentinel Score formula is defined in SENTINEL_PROJECT_PLAN.md under "Sentinel Score Formula"
- All scoring functions return 0-100 integers
- All scoring functions clamp output: Math.max(0, Math.min(100, score))
- Score weights must sum to 100
- When computing scores, always handle missing data gracefully (default to neutral 50)
- Every score computation must create a signal_snapshot for performance tracking

## UI/Design Rules
- DARK THEME ONLY. Design tokens are in SENTINEL_PROJECT_PLAN.md under "Design Tokens"
- Use JetBrains Mono for all data/numbers/tickers
- Use Inter for all labels/descriptions/body text
- Color coding is absolute: green = bullish, red = bearish, amber = caution, purple = AI
- Every component must handle: loading state, error state, and empty state
- Tables must be sortable by clicking column headers
- All prices/values use lib/utils/format.ts for consistent formatting
- No component should exceed 200 lines. Extract sub-components if needed.

## Testing Rules
- Write tests for ALL scoring functions (lib/analyzers/*.ts, lib/scoring.ts)
- Write tests for ALL API wrapper functions (lib/financial-datasets.ts, etc.)
- Use vitest as the test runner
- Mock API calls in tests — never make real API calls in test suite
- For scoring functions: test edge cases (all zeros, max values, missing data)
- For flag detection: test each flag individually AND combinations

## Performance Tracking Rules
- EVERY alert trigger must call snapshotSignal() before posting to Discord
- Forward returns are filled by cron — never block on forward price lookups
- Minimum sample size for trusting a signal: N >= 30
- Always compute alpha (stock return - SPY return), not just raw return

## Git Rules
- Commit after each completed task (not after each file)
- Commit messages: "feat: [sprint]-[task] description" or "fix: description"
- Never commit .env.local or API keys
- Use feature branches per sprint: sprint-1/data-pipeline, sprint-2/screener-ui, etc.

## What NOT to do
- Do NOT use localStorage or sessionStorage (not needed, server-side data)
- Do NOT install UI component libraries (shadcn, MUI, etc.) — build minimal custom components
- Do NOT use Redux or Zustand — React Server Components + URL state is sufficient
- Do NOT use Prisma — Supabase client is the ORM
- Do NOT over-abstract early — concrete > clever
- Do NOT skip error handling to "come back to it later"
- Do NOT write components longer than 200 lines
- Do NOT make Claude API calls without try/catch on JSON parsing
